![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/57627e1c-8395-4555-9383-deaf85d1bfc8/14179.jpg?format=original) ![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/bc450765-361c-4efb-b9c4-33566123bd53/14187.jpg?format=original)

Roman Reigns opens the show to an incredible ovation. He says they sound the way they always did but life is not the same. He needs to be truthful to himself.

Cody Rhodes predicted this downfall would happen(loud boos). He is not the same man he was at his peak. Roman says the Vision has made sure of this.

Roman says he's proud of his cousin Jey Uso. Anyone who questions Jey is wrong and needs to accept that Roman’s time will come later.

Paul Heyman and Bronson Reed interrupt. Heyman says five years ago, he became the Wiseman. They built the Bloodline together.

But Roman is alone now because of himself. Paul Heyman says he STILL loves his Tribal Chief. Which is why he's going to disrespect him.

Roman Reigns needs tough love. But Heyman knows he's not man enough to beat it into Roman but Bronson Reed is.

Roman calls Heyman a dumbass who's going to kiss his ass on Sunday after he whoops Bronson’s ass.

Bronson says Roman’s Samoan tribe was pampered but Bronson’s Samoan tribe was exiled to Australia. Roman’s tribal tats are paid for. Bronson’s are earned.

Roman says hold up, this guy's Samoan??? If he's Samoan than his ass belongs to Roman Reigns. Since they're cut from the same cloth, why doesn't he just bring the shoes down and call it even.

Bronson comes down to the ring and they brawl to the commercial break

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a4b12363-2a11-4b5e-9036-5c709b11dda4/14190.jpg?format=original)

